Combat\par
\b0\i0\f1\fs20 Physical attacks have a chance to hit dependant on the attacker's dexterity, hit roll, and weapon, and the defenders dexterity. If an attack hits, the defenders armour class gives a chance for the blow to be deflected or absorbed. If damage is dealt,\par
damage = (attacker_dam + weapon)*attacker_str/defender_con\par
Magical attacks are dependant on the spell, but are typicaly related to caster_ perception/target_perception, levels of both players, and target saves. Spell saves are not level dependent, but only highly specialised players will be able to have good saves.\par
\b\i\f0\fs24 Levels\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\qj\b0\i0\f1\fs20 Because our player statistics work differently to most MUDs, so does the amount you receive each level. Infact most stats are not calculated upon leveling, but are rather generated by a formula dependent on a persons race and specialisation. These are modified every time you level or specialise, but are not random. This means that leveling equipment and optimisation provide no benefit, and charcter diversity in stats comes purely from level race and specialisation. Indeed we shall not be allowing things such as strength modifying equipment. Each time a player levels they will recieve 100 pracs to spend on skills. Their hitpoints and energy will also be modified to reflect their experience (HP = 500 + 10*level + specialisation_mod*level) (Energy = 500 + 10*level + specialisation_mod*level). Some specialisations such as soldier will give bonus HP. All specialisations modify player characteristics Str, Con, Perception. We believe this will be both fairer, and take away focus from OOC leveling concerns.\par
