\pard\sb240\sa60\keepn\nowidctlpar\b\i\f0\fs24\page Magic\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\qj\b0\i0\f1\fs20 The magic in our world will involve the drawing of energy from potentials that exist in almost infinite abundance within nature.  The drawing of such energy and the conversion of it into tangible and useable forms will require some form of exertion by the caster, such as an incantation, gestures, phsysic force or rituals.  The five potentials that can be tapped relate to spirit, air, water, earth and fire.  Manipulating one or more of the potentials allows people to bring into being events, energies and forms that would otherwise be impossible and unstable.  As the potentials are nearly infinite, the loss of control over a redirection, or failure to harness an energy leak is both unpredictable and dangerous. Perhaps the most terrifying potential to unleash randomly is the potential of spirit, as it results in freedom for those of the 'beyond world' to take form in the physical world. Fortunatley existance in reality is painful for daemons as it is a distortion of their true elemental makeup. For this same reason angles rarely stay long in the physical world.  The ability to interact with the potentials is a mental one, which can be learnt with dilligence. The actual manipulation requires different approaches depending on the desired effect. For instance enchanters mostly use incantations, while necromancers often are more ritualistic. The one exception is Alchemy which technically requires only dilligence and attention to detail, however in practise an excellent mind is still required to remember and execute the concoction to perfection.\b\i\f0\fs24\par
\b0\i0\f1\fs20\par
\par
There are five essential potentials involved in our world\rquote s magic:\par
\pard {\pntext\f2\'b7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent360{\pntxtb\'b7}}\fi-360\li360\nowidctlpar\qj\tx360 spirit\par
{\pntext\f2\'b7\tab}fire\par
{\pntext\f2\'b7\tab}water\par
{\pntext\f2\'b7\tab}earth\par
{\pntext\f2\'b7\tab}air\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\qj\par
Magic draws upon these in differing proportions. Certain mages steal the energy, others use it, and some channel it. A spells effectiveness is typically calcuated by taking into account the casters level, the targets saves, and the ratio of casters perception to targets perception. As players have individual saves for each element, spells which opperate on different elemental potentials will have different outcomes for each target. Saves will be affected by equipment, spells and skills, eg: firey shield will increase fire saves but lower water saves, in such a way that\par
it will be hard to maximise all saves simultaneously.\par
\par
Another interesting possibility is time splicing magic, however this remains to be discovered.\par
\pard\sb240\sa60\keepn\nowidctlpar\qj\b\i\f0\fs24 Death\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\qj\b0\i0\f1\fs20 When a player dies, their soul can return randomly within the area. In this spirit form they are translucent, undetectable, floating, deaf and dumb. The spirit form lasts 50 hours or until the command \lquote reform\rquote  is typed. When a soul reforms to all the five elements of a pre-existent living being, it returns to its former shape, however the being suffers from \lquote fine alignment syndrome\rquote  (5+level hours recovery period), and the soul potential ages. During the recovery period a PC suffers severe restrictions, perhaps inability to use skills. If the soul looses its individuality through age death is permanent.\par
\par
Possible IC explination: When you die you are drawn toward the 'world beyond', however because of the Coming, spirits now have a stronger link into the more physical elements. Your death causes a disturbance in the spirit potential which if resisted can allow the soul of a person to remain in the physical world. Because this is essentially a leak in the spirit potential, you could end up anywhere nearby. As for all spirits this is a painful process which is reflected in age and a recovery period. If the pain and age becomes too great, your link to past existance is forgotten or lost and your soul looses its individuality. Only souls which retain a link to their past have any hope of reforming with the other elements.\par
