\b Imolean\b0\par
The Imolian race rose up from the watery depth of the oceans and appeared around the south eastern seaboard of Lu'Tamohr around the year 1500BG.  While still humanoid in appearance their feet exist in various levels of aquatic function, from slight webbing between the toes to large toeless fins.  Their ears follow a similar trend, some with small gill slits behind them, others with large gill slits and largely non existant ears.  The Imolian folk brought knowledge of the depths to the inhabitants of Lu'Tamohr and were largely peaceful.\par
Currently the Imolean folk are scattered throughout the isle with no centralised powerbase.  They are a magical race, but their love of peace in general seems to discourage them from pursuing the magical arts.\par
\par
They fled in the year 1000BG after attempting to stall the Eldern forces as they swarmed across the ----- river. Imolian culture was and is rumoured to be highly structured and truely noble, aboring war. For this reason they fought to prevent the inevitable conqure of their Panan neighbours, but were defeated and forced into slavery, never to return to their bretheren in the deep.\par
\par
Only fifth generation and later Imolian's remain at and near Lu'Tamohr. Those who have gained their freedom know not the way back to the pods of their ancestors. The ledgends of their culture are all but lost in myth. Many doubt that links to their past will ever be revived, or that if they are that their ancesotrial culture will want to have anything to do with them.\b\par
