Malandrin\b0\par
With the arrival of the Imolian folk in 1800BG, many of the Rehan folk grew suspicious of them and the results of cross breeding. They moved away from the large cities and travelled north into the high country, far from the water and Imolian. They made hard lives for themselves in the mountains.  They turned towards the stone foundations of the Malandrin Range for gems and minerals.  Indeed, the construction of their crowning acheivement Cora'Tyl was based on a large stockpile of gems and minerals.  Cora'Tyl owes its continued existence to the hardiness and ferocity with which the Malandrin inhaibitants guard their city walls, and its ability to easily trade its hard sought gems for other commodities not easily obtained within the range.\par
\par
Their growing suspicion of the thriving Cvin race was vindicated when the invasion was launched. The Cvin had fought its way, largely unresisted apart from at the river, to the mountains. There it met organised defenses, walls, castles and well armed military. The Eldren were never able to sustain any control over the mountains, because of the preparations, and the extent to which the attacking forces had been spread.\par
